                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is little reason to be charming level 70 mobs. Relative level is the biggest determinant of charm duration. A charmed level 70 pet still only hits for 260 max in omens, or 100 dps assuming you dont haste it (unless you are suicidal). You have to compare this to the 50dps your animation will be doing against the mobs and the damage your nukes do from the 910 mana you save from not charming.
<br />
Or warriors do 250 dps while tanking, our rogues do around 400 dps the relative increase of 50 dps over your sword pet is not worth the risk. When charm breaks its going to kill you or the cleric, the group will not want these risks for such a trivial increase in dps, even a bard melee far outdamages our charmed pets. So yes its a waste of a rune, whoever decided the new damage table at SoE should be fired.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
